Vice President Kamala Harris met with leaders from Guatemala to discuss the root causes of migration from the Northern Triangle, particularly focusing on corruption and the violation of the rule of law. Harris, a former attorney, emphasized the importance of fighting for justice and against injustice. She acknowledged that corruption hinders economic development and serves as a deterrent to financial and economic investment in the region. Harris stressed the need for judicial independence and accountability in government. She expressed her belief that providing people with a sense of hope and a commitment to rooting out corruption will encourage them to stay in their communities. The Vice President thanked the leaders for joining the discussion and looked forward to an open conversation.